    "author_association": "NONE",
    "body": "### Problem\n\n### Summary With the Neovim 0.12 released version for Windows, xxd.exe present within the zip is detected as Trojan and defender is blocking the application.   \n\n\n ### Impact Neovim 0.12 can't be used in windows\n\n### Steps to reproduce\n\nDownload the nvim-win64 from the release for 0.12 and scan with defender\n\n### Expected behavior\n\nNo issues with Defender scan\n\n### Nvim version (nvim -v)\n\n0.12\n\n### Vim (not Nvim) behaves the same?\n\nNo\n\n### Operating system/version\n\nWindows\n\n### Terminal name/version\n\n-\n\n### $TERM environment variable\n\n-\n\n### Installation\n\nInstaller from Github",
    "closed_at": null,
    "closed_by": null,
    "comment_data": [
        {
            "author_association": "MEMBER",
            "body": "The full source of `xxd.exe` is here: https://github.com/neovim/neovim/blob/master/src/xxd/xxd.c \n\nIf antivirus is flagging it, it's a bug in the antivirus. Can you please try [reporting the false positive to Defender](https://learn.microsoft.com/en-us/defender-endpoint/defender-endpoint-false-positives-negatives) so they stop flagging it?\n\nHowever we could plan to [sign it](https://github.com/neovim/neovim/issues/5433#issuecomment-486724845) once we get around to doing that ...",
